						               													<description>In the year 2266, the world is controlled by a facist police state.  Peace, love, unity, and respect have all been made illegal.  Finding the relics of reggae in the ruins of the old world, a circle of youths rediscovers the power of music.  They plan to coordinate an enormous underground dance party to return the message of nonviolent resistance back to the people.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Reggae Revolution is a cooperative card game for 1 to 6 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players work together to bring the message of peace and love back to the world.  In the game are four suits: peace, love, unity, and respect.  Players try to use these cards to collect sets in the score area to win the game.  But, at the beginning of each player's turn, a villain card pops out and makes the player discards all cards of a suit that the villain supresses.  Instead of fighting the villains, the players must sway them by giving them cards from their deck.  If the player does not have enough, the villain stays in play.  As the villains stack up, the players must discard more and more cards from their hand.  If the villains ever supress all four suits, peace, love, unity, and respect, then no one has any cards and the villains win the game!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Fight the power!  Join the resistance!  And bring peace and love back to the people!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
